cs.SY, cs.NE, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO

The paper proposes a novel control architecture for adaptive control of continuous-time systems using an external working memory. This involves the use of neural networks and machine learning techniques, which are commonly associated with the sub-categories of cs.SY (Systems and Control), cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), cs.LG (Machine Learning), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper specifically considers the application of the proposed architecture to a robot arm controller, which falls under the sub-category of cs.RO (Robotics). Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.SY, followed by cs.NE, cs.LG, cs.AI, and cs.RO.
